Replace the hardcoded port with an environment variable:

```javascript
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;

app.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`);
});
```

This change allows the port to be:
- Set via environment variable (e.g., `PORT=8000 node app.js`)
- Configured by deployment platforms like Heroku, AWS, etc.
- Kept at the default 3000 if no environment variable is specified

